<item>
            <title>[FLINK-15196] The mesos.resourcemanager.tasks.cpus configuration does not work as expectation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-15196</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I tried to set the number of CPU of Mesos workers, I found the &quot;mesos.resourcemanager.tasks.cpus&quot; configuration does not work anymore. After passing over  recent commits, I guess the root cause is &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/10146&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;FLINK-14188&lt;/a&gt;. The configuration key in MesosTaskManagerParameters#getCpuCores is incorrect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=azagrebin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;azagrebin&quot;&gt;azagrebin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
